004package mkt;
005
006import java.util.ArrayList;
007import kut.Js;
008import kut.Arr;
009
010/** Result of 'Strategy.xxxSimple2' group. */
011public class StGroup2Rs {
012  /**
013   * Number of sales.<br>
014   * One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
015   * */
016  public final int[] sales;
017  /**
018   * Cash + withdrawals + portfolio evaluated with closes. <br>
019   * One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
020   */
021  public final double[] assets;
022  /**
023   * Cash + withdrawals + portfolio evaluated with prices. <br>
024   * One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
025   */
026  public final double[] accs;
027  /**
028   * Cash + withdrawals + portfolio evaluated with references.<br>
029   * One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
030   */
031  public final double[] rfAssets;
032  /**
033   * Profits ratio average. Portfolio evaluated with closes.<br>
034   * One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
035   */
036  public final double[] profits;
037  /**
038   * Profits ratio average. Portfolio evaluated with references.<br>
039   * One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
040   */
041  public final double[] rfProfits;
042
043  /**
044   * Constructor.
045   * @param sales Number of sales.<br>
046   *        One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
047   * @param assets Cash + withdrawals + portfolio evaluated with closes.<br>
048   *        One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
049   * @param accs Cash + withdrawals + portfolio evaluated with prices.<br>
050   *        One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
051   * @param rfAssets Cash + withdrawals + portfolio evaluated with references.<br>
052   *        One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
053   * @param profits Profits ratio average. Portfolio evaluated with closes.<br>
054   *        One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
055   * @param rfProfits Profits ratio average. Portfolio evaluated with references.<br>
056   *        One entry for each Parameter in the same order.
057   */
058  public StGroup2Rs (
059    int[] sales, double[] assets, double[] accs, double[] rfAssets,
060    double[] profits, double[] rfProfits
061  ) {
062    this.sales = sales;
063    this.assets = assets;
064    this.accs = accs;
065    this.rfAssets = rfAssets;
066    this.profits = profits;
067    this.rfProfits = rfProfits;
068  }
069
070  /**
071   * Returns object JSONized.
072   * @param o Ditto.
073   * @return Ditto.
074   */
075  public static String toJs (StGroup2Rs o) {
076    return Js.w(Arr.mk(
077      Js.w(Arr.map(Arr.mk(o.sales), Js::w)),
078      Js.w(Arr.map(Arr.mk(o.assets), Js::w)),
079      Js.w(Arr.map(Arr.mk(o.accs), Js::w)),
080      Js.w(Arr.map(Arr.mk(o.rfAssets), Js::w)),
081      Js.w(Arr.map(Arr.mk(o.profits), Js::w)),
082      Js.w(Arr.map(Arr.mk(o.rfProfits), Js::w))
083    ));
084  }
085
086  /**
087   * Returns object from JSON.
088   * @param js JSON string.
089   * @return Ditto.
090   */
091  public static StGroup2Rs fromJs (String js) {
092    ArrayList<String> a = Js.ra(js);
093    return new StGroup2Rs(
094      Arr.toInts(Arr.map(Js.ra(a.get(0)), (v) -> (int)Js.rn(v))),
095      Arr.toDoubles(Arr.map(Js.ra(a.get(1)), Js::rn)),
096      Arr.toDoubles(Arr.map(Js.ra(a.get(2)), Js::rn)),
097      Arr.toDoubles(Arr.map(Js.ra(a.get(3)), Js::rn)),
098      Arr.toDoubles(Arr.map(Js.ra(a.get(4)), Js::rn)),
099      Arr.toDoubles(Arr.map(Js.ra(a.get(5)), Js::rn))
100    );
101  }
102}
